FREMONT, Calif. and NEWARK, Calif., March 14, 2013 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) Oplink Communications, Inc. (OPLK), a leading provider of design, integration and optical manufacturing solutions (OMS) for optical networking components, modules and subsystems, and Kaiam Corporation, a leader in hybrid Photonic Integrated Circuit (PIC) technology, today announced a joint demonstration of the 100Gbps 10x10 40km CFP transceiver technologies for extended reach (ER) 100Gbps applications at OFC/NFOEC 2013 in Anaheim, CAThe 10x10 40km CFP modules, jointly developed by the two companies, enable cost effective deployments of 100G for interdata center and broadband backhaul applications.
